      "body" : "Well, it should be pretty simple to make a .bat file that changes a environment variable and launches `bitcoin.exe`. I don't use windows myself, so I can't test, but copy-pasting this into a bat in the same directory as bitcoin.exe should do the job:\r\n\r\n    @echo off\r\n    SET LANG=en_US.UTF-8\r\n    bitcoin.exe\r\n\r\n\r\n",
